# Dev fallbacks for the app's config loader. Copy to .env (gitignored) and fill in.
# Contract (doctrine wiki ops/07): the secret name IS the config field name. In
# prod every field is a file /run/secrets/<field> (Docker secret); in local
# dev the fallback is the UPPERCASED env var, loaded from .env.

# DB_URL=postgres://{{DB_USER}}:{{DB_USER}}@localhost:5432/{{DB_NAME}}
# SESSION_SECRET=<generate one: openssl rand -hex 32>
# APP_BASE_URL=http://localhost:<dev-port>

# Convention: the project's migration tooling should read DATABASE_URL (not
# DB_URL) in dev/CI, and fall back to /run/secrets/db_url inside the Swarm:
# DATABASE_URL=postgres://{{DB_USER}}:{{DB_USER}}@localhost:5432/{{DB_NAME}}
